text.tspan: Black, green, and white tea all come from the same plant –
camellia sinensis. The various types come from different
harvesting times and the drying and oxidation process.
Black tea leaves are oxidized the longest of all teas,
producing high levels of tannins that give it its dark
color and slightly astringent flavor.the tea bush.
